# PhotoEdit clang-tidy config — advisory developer aid (run in CI, but not a hard gate).
# Kept small and high-signal: no WarningsAsErrors, and no readability-identifier-naming
# (the codebase uses the kCamelCase constant convention, which that check would flag
# wholesale). The CI "clang-tidy (advisory)" lane runs this and surfaces findings; it does
# not block merges. See docs/04-coding-standards.md.

---
Checks: >
  -*,
  bugprone-*,
  performance-*,
  modernize-*,
  -modernize-use-trailing-return-type,
  -modernize-avoid-c-arrays,
  -modernize-use-designated-initializers,
  -bugprone-easily-swappable-parameters

WarningsAsErrors: ''

HeaderFilterRegex: 'src/core/.*'

CheckOptions:
  - key:   modernize-use-auto.IgnoreMacros
    value: 'true'
  - key:   performance-unnecessary-value-param.AllowedTypes
    value: 'std::function;'
...
